<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>, chargé.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-08"><hi rend="italic">August 8,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 912.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 1868, of June 18 last, in regard to the seizure of land belonging to
                            the American Presbyterian Mission in Hainan.</p>
                        <p>The opinion expressed in your communication to the consul at Canton is
                            judicious and in the line of the treaty stipulation requiring mutual
                            agreement as to mission sites.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>